    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, r u saying the \"inefficient\" part is just wrong? i thought there were actual economic arguments about how much it costs taxpayers and how it might slow down innovation. if it's a \"right,\" then how do you handle the downsides? isn't it a valid political stance to worry about govt spending?",
