      "content": "i hear you, but it feels like you're dismissing the whole \"limited government\" side of the debate. some people believe that giving the state total control over healthcare is a dangerous precedent that goes against individual liberty. can't there be a legitimate moral argument for private choice and competition over a state-run system, or is that also just \"overstated\"?",
